{
  "stem": "20609.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this was a farming community and since we were the nearest camp there, they transport all the animals-- the horses and-- into Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So-- [DRINKS] Now all of a sudden, everybody gets shipped out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We're down to about 20,000 people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This is a camp a week earlier, we were 75,000 people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "All of a sudden, we're down to 15,000, 18,000 people-- I don't know the exact [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "All of a sudden, I got assigned to the stable because I-- I didn't operate-- I handled horses in Denmark on a farm so that Henry, my buddy, we get all-- all-- all of a sudden, all of us, the old gang now get the great jobs.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because all the initial teamsters, the guy who had these now were transporting bread.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I had a team of horses.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Every morning, I took-- I picked up all the dead bodies, put them into the crematory, and delivered them there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and in the afternoon, I might have transported bread.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I had another break.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Occasionally, I went out with one of the SS to-- to the nearest city outside where he picked up rations for himself in the-- in the NCO club or whatever they had there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And-- and occasionally, I had a good one-- he gave me a piece of sausage or something like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And if you had a bad one, he hit you a couple of times just to keep you straight.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But in principle, it was a good job.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The problem was we-- we saw the SS, the commandant, every day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because A, he had a horse he was riding, a black horse.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I think it was one of the oldest horses in the world because it was-- it was not a wild horse.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
